Problem
Given a string, replace all vowels with '#'.

Input Format
A single string containing alphabets.

Output Format
A string with all vowels replaced by '#'.

Sample Inputs & Outputs
Sample Input 1
Hello

Sample Output 1
H#ll#

Sample Input 2
world

Sample Output 2
w#rld

Constraints
The length of the string is at most 10^4.

Code
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Replace {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        String inputString = scanner.nextLine(); // Read the input string

        // Replace vowels with "#"
        String replaceString = inputString.replaceAll("[aeiouAEIOU]", "#");

        System.out.println(replaceString); // Print the Replace string    
    }
}
